# Build-time DEFAULT Jellyfin server URL. Intentionally EMPTY in committed
# source — the maintainer's server address must not ship in the public repo or
# the App Store build. Set it where it belongs instead:
#   - local dev / e2e:  .env.local (gitignored)
#   - CI:               the VITE_JELLYFIN_URL GitHub secret
#   - self-host deploy: the JELLYFIN_URL env on the container (runtime config.js,
#                       via deploy/runtime-config.sh) — no rebuild needed
# Empty here means the app ships with no default and users enter their own
# Jellyfin server on the sign-in screen (the Server field).
VITE_JELLYFIN_URL=

# Optional DEFAULT marlin-search (Meilisearch) indexer URL for faster search.
# EMPTY here — never commit a real address/port. Search stays on Jellyfin's
# native endpoint until this is set OR the user configures a URL in Settings.
# Set it where it belongs:
#   - local dev / e2e:  .env.local (gitignored)
#   - self-host deploy: the MARLIN_SEARCH_URL env → runtime config.js
# The auth token is NEVER a build var — it's entered in Settings, stored on-device.
VITE_MARLIN_URL=
